  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Choice of arterial cannulation site during cardiac surgery is controversial. Some physicians&#xD;
      in our institution prefer radial artery site, others prefer aortic site (via femoral artery&#xD;
      or brachial artery). The investigators aim to compare these two strategies for vasopressor&#xD;
      requirement. The study hypothesis is that radial artery cannulation is associated with a&#xD;
      larger dose of vasopressor due aortic to radial arterial pressure gradient phenomenon.&#xD;
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
